{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a7c1f2e4-savnspend-api-v1",
    "name": "Save n Spend API",
    "description": "Local API for the Save n Spend app (Express + Mongo, port 7019).\n\n## Setup\n1. Start the API: `cd apps/api && npm run dev`\n2. (Optional) seed test data: `npm run seed` — creates **sagnik@email.com / sagnik123** and **bipasha@email.com / bipasha123**\n3. Run **Auth → Login (Sagnik)** once — its test script stores `accessToken` as a collection variable and every other request inherits it via Bearer auth.\n\n## Conventions\n- Every response uses the envelope `{ success, statusCode, message, data }`.\n- **Money is integer paise** (₹1 = 100 paise). `amount` is always positive; `type` gives the sign.\n- All `/:id` routes are ownership-scoped: another user's id returns 404, leaking nothing.\n- Create/POST helper scripts store `accountId` / `categoryId` / `transactionId` collection variables so the `/:id` requests chain without copy-pasting ids.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{accessToken}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "HOST", "value": "http://localhost:7019", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "BASE_URL", "value": "{{HOST}}/api/v1", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accessToken", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "accountId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "categoryId", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "transactionId", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
