    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Register does NOT auto-login (separate flows by design). Login's test script auto-saves `accessToken`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"email\": \"test@email.com\",\n  \"password\": \"test1234\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/register", "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"], "path": ["auth", "register"] },
            "description": "Body: `name` (min 2 chars), `email`, `password` (min 8 chars).\n\nAtomic register-seeding inside a Mongo transaction: creates the user → a starter **Cash** account → copies the default category set (per-user copies) → sets `prefs.defaultAccount` to the Cash account. All-or-nothing.\n\nDoes NOT return a token — log in afterwards."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "POST", "header": [], "url": { "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/register", "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"], "path": ["auth", "register"] } },
              "status": "Created",
              "code": 201,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"statusCode\": 201,\n  \"message\": \"User registered successfully!\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"_id\": \"6a568001927536ee5cba3c9d\",\n    \"name\": \"Test User\",\n    \"email\": \"test@email.com\",\n    \"currency\": \"INR\",\n    \"prefs\": {\n      \"defaultAccount\": \"6a568002927536ee5cba3cbd\",\n      \"budgetCycleDay\": 1,\n      \"notifications\": {\n        \"enabled\": true,\n        \"billReminderLead\": 3,\n        \"budgetAlerts\": true,\n        \"goalMilestones\": true,\n        \"weeklySummary\": true\n      }\n    },\n    \"createdAt\": \"2026-07-14T18:29:22.041Z\",\n    \"updatedAt\": \"2026-07-14T18:29:22.041Z\"\n  }\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "409 Conflict (duplicate email)",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "POST", "header": [], "url": { "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/register", "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"], "path": ["auth", "register"] } },
              "status": "Conflict",
              "code": 409,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"statusCode\": 409,\n  \"message\": \"Duplicate value for a unique field\",\n  \"data\": null\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login (Sagnik)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Auto-populate the collection's accessToken from a successful login.",
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200 && json?.data?.accessToken) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accessToken', json.data.accessToken);",
                  "  console.log('accessToken saved — all requests are now authenticated.');",
                  "} else {",
                  "  console.warn('Login failed — accessToken NOT updated.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"sagnik@email.com\",\n  \"password\": \"sagnik123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{BASE_URL}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "description": "Seed test user 1. On 200, the test script stores `data.accessToken` into the `accessToken` collection variable — every protected request inherits it via the collection-level Bearer auth. Token expiry: 7 days."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
